.TH "intel_atomic_setup_scalers" 9 "intel_atomic_setup_scalers" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
intel_atomic_setup_scalers \- setup scalers for crtc per staged requests
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" intel_atomic_setup_scalers
.BI "(struct drm_i915_private *dev_priv "  ","
.BI "struct intel_crtc *intel_crtc "  ","
.BI "struct intel_crtc_state *crtc_state "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "dev_priv" 12
i915 device
.IP "intel_crtc" 12
intel crtc
.IP "crtc_state" 12
incoming crtc_state to validate and setup scalers
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
This function sets up scalers based on staged scaling requests for
a \fIcrtc\fP and its planes. It is called from crtc level check path. If request
is a supportable request, it attaches scalers to requested planes and crtc.

This function takes into account the current scaler(s) in use by any planes
not being part of this atomic state
.SH "RETURN"
0 - scalers were setup succesfully
error code - otherwise
